        public InsertData visit(ASTInsertData node,
               Object data)
                 throws VisitorException
        Note: Variables in QuadDatas are disallowed in INSERT DATA requests (see Notes 8 in the grammar). That is, the INSERT DATA statement only allows to insert ground triples. Blank nodes in QuadDatas are assumed to be disjoint from the blank nodes in the Graph Store, i.e., will be inserted with "fresh" blank nodes.

      • visit

        public DeleteInsertGraph visit(ASTDeleteWhere node,
                      Object data)
                        throws VisitorException
        This handles the "DELETE WHERE" syntax short hand. 
         DELETE WHERE  QuadPattern
        This is similar to a CONSTRUCT without an explicit template. The WHERE clause provides both the pattern to match and the template for the quads to be removed.

        Note: The grammar production for the WHERE clause for the DELETE WHERE shortcut form is the same production that is used for the DELETE and INSERT clauses. This results in a QuadData object containing StatementPatternNodes. That object must be transformed into a JoinGroupNode in order to be valid as a WHERE clause.

        Specified by:
        visit in interface SyntaxTreeBuilderVisitor
        Overrides:
        visit in class ASTVisitorBase
        Throws:
        VisitorException
        See Also:
        (DELETE WHERE fails with Java AssertionError)

      • visit

        public DeleteInsertGraph visit(ASTModify node,
                      Object data)
                        throws VisitorException
        The DELETE/INSERT operation can be used to remove or add triples from/to the Graph Store based on bindings for a query pattern specified in a WHERE clause: 
         ( WITH IRIref )?
 ( ( DeleteClause InsertClause? ) | InsertClause )
 ( USING ( NAMED )? IRIref )*
 WHERE GroupGraphPattern
        The DeleteClause and InsertClause forms can be broken down as follows: 
         DeleteClause ::= DELETE  QuadPattern 
 InsertClause ::= INSERT  QuadPattern
        Specified by:
        visit in interface SyntaxTreeBuilderVisitor
        Overrides:
        visit in class ASTVisitorBase
